</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[168,776,714,1308]" pageId="21" pageNumber="500">
In this species the posterior margin of the corium is strongly sinuous, and the lateral angles are produced. In males the posterior dorsal side of the proctiger lack distinct spines, and the dorsolateral parameral processes from caudal view are inclined dorsad and rounded at the apex. In females the length of the first gonocoxae from base at meson to posterior apex is less than 
<quantity box="[640,725,1217,1241]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="500" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
, and the length of the second gonocoxae at meson less than 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="500" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Eger JE" box="[223,339,1284,1308]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the New York Entomological Society" pageId="21" pageNumber="500" pagination="224 - 259" part="86" refId="ref30537" refString="Eger JE (1978) Revision of the genus Loxa (Hemiptera: Pentatomidae). Journal of the New York Entomological Society 86 (3): 224 - 259." title="Revision of the genus Loxa (Hemiptera: Pentatomidae)" type="journal article" year="1978">Eger 1978</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
